1
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:27,694
(USAGI) <i>Don't worry, I'll find a</i>
<i>way to make you better again, I</i>
<i>promise.</i>

2
00:00:28,028 --> 00:00:31,431
(USAGI) <i>And protect the planet</i>
<i>at the same time.</i>

3
00:00:37,504 --> 00:00:38,772
(USAGI) <i>Chibi Moon!</i>

4
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:40,974
Chibi Moon, can you hear me?

5
00:00:42,008 --> 00:00:45,445
Hang on! I'll get you out of
there, don't you worry!

6
00:00:46,947 --> 00:00:48,281
[grunt] Whoah...

7
00:00:48,348 --> 00:00:49,282
Sailor Moon!

8
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:51,618
Chibi Moon!

9
00:00:54,521 --> 00:01:01,635
[laughing] Pegasus and his
host... are now in our
possession!

10
00:01:04,638 --> 00:01:05,806
Pegasus and...

11
00:01:05,872 --> 00:01:06,807
...his host?

12
00:01:08,074 --> 00:01:12,646
Chibi Moon... Chibi Moon!

13
00:01:12,979 --> 00:01:18,484
(THE AMAZONESS QUARTET) <i>Always</i>
<i>remember not to forget. A</i>
<i>child's dream is a dream they</i>
<i>should never get.</i>

14
00:01:18,585 --> 00:01:20,821
<i>Always remember not to forget...</i>

15
00:03:00,661 --> 00:03:03,604
(USAGI) <i>Labyrinth of</i>
<i>Mirrors: Chibi Moon Captured</i>

16
00:03:14,214 --> 00:03:16,049
(USAGI) Another fork in the
road...

17
00:03:16,149 --> 00:03:17,951
(MAKOTO) Which way do we go?

18
00:03:22,723 --> 00:03:23,456
That way.

19
00:03:23,857 --> 00:03:24,625
Right.

20
00:03:26,126 --> 00:03:28,995
Stay sharp. I sense a massive
aura of darkness coming from
this direction.

21
00:03:35,802 --> 00:03:37,971
Ahhh! Omph!

22
00:03:39,806 --> 00:03:41,141
Now where am I?

23
00:03:43,744 --> 00:03:43,977
[gasp]

24
00:03:47,180 --> 00:03:48,815
The Stallion Reve...

25
00:03:52,886 --> 00:03:55,989
Pegasus?... [gasp]

26
00:04:04,738 --> 00:04:05,506
Huh?

27
00:04:16,016 --> 00:04:16,683
[gasp]

28
00:04:22,222 --> 00:04:26,026
[gasp] Helios...?

29
00:04:44,077 --> 00:04:45,546
[blushing]

30
00:04:49,783 --> 00:04:50,884
Is that you?

31
00:04:57,090 --> 00:05:02,736
Nice to meet you! Must've been
really terrible, being all
alone in a place like this.

32
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:06,072
Hang on, I'll get you out of
there.

33
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:08,609
(QUEEN NEHALENNIA) <i>I can't let</i>
<i>you do that.</i>

34
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:09,910
[gasp]

35
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:17,083
[gasps and straining]

36
00:05:17,818 --> 00:05:22,255
So, it was you all along. You
were Pegasus' host.

37
00:05:22,623 --> 00:05:23,256
Who're you?

38
00:05:25,091 --> 00:05:30,764
I am Nehalennia... Queen
Nehalennia, ruler of the Dead
Moon.

39
00:05:30,964 --> 00:05:31,765
[gasp]

40
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:36,269
Some queen.

41
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:40,774
Why are you keeping Helios in a
dark place like this?

42
00:05:42,275 --> 00:05:46,112
You can't even imagine the true
depths of darkness.

43
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:51,852
A child who's walked in light
all your life, you could never
know how I feel.

44
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:54,287
It all began eons ago...

45
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:06,640
<i>Back then, there was a kingdom</i>
<i>on the Moon, filled with</i>
<i>light... It was known as Silver</i>
<i>Millennium.</i>

46
00:06:07,007 --> 00:06:07,874
[gasp]

47
00:06:09,409 --> 00:06:12,813
<i>This kingdom flourished under</i>
<i>the rule of a queen named</i>
<i>Serenity.</i>

48
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:26,326
<i>But there was another queen,</i>
<i>the Queen of Darkness... and she</i>
<i>observed Silver Millennium from</i>
<i>her dark and cold asteroid.</i>

49
00:06:31,431 --> 00:06:36,169
<i>The Queen of Darkness envied the</i>
<i>prosperity of the Moon</i>
<i>Kingdom...</i>

50
00:06:36,336 --> 00:06:40,340
<i>and she yearned to find some way</i>
<i>of making that kingdom her own.</i>

51
00:06:41,441 --> 00:06:47,781
<i>In time, the Queen of Darkness</i>
<i>learned of a mystical stone</i>
<i>possessing unimaginable</i>
<i>powers...</i>

52
00:06:47,881 --> 00:06:54,187
<i>With this stone's power, she</i>
<i>could usurp the Queen of the</i>
<i>Moon's throne... More than</i>
<i>that...</i>

53
00:06:54,254 --> 00:06:56,857
<i>she could eventually rule</i>
<i>the universe!</i>

54
00:07:00,794 --> 00:07:10,210
<i>This stone, the Golden Crystal,</i>
<i>was located in a sacred place on</i>
<i>Earth... where it was protected</i>
<i>by a young man.</i>

55
00:07:27,093 --> 00:07:27,894
[gasp]

56
00:07:29,295 --> 00:07:33,233
The Queen of Darkness
experienced emotions she could
not comprehend.

57
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:38,905
She found herself desiring not
just the stone... but the young
man as well.

58
00:07:39,506 --> 00:07:47,413
<i>She approached the young man and</i>
<i>proposed that they rule the</i>
<i>universe together, using the</i>
<i>power of the Golden Crystal.</i>

59
00:07:49,115 --> 00:07:52,252
<i>It's thye Golden Crystal that</i>
<i>chooses its owner...</i>

60
00:07:54,087 --> 00:08:02,268
<i>If you possess a beautiful</i>
<i>dream... then you can acquire</i>
<i>this stone... However... if you</i>
<i>do not...</i>

61
00:08:08,542 --> 00:08:15,115
<i>If you do not... then you will</i>
<i>be punished for possessing an</i>
<i>evil heart.</i>

62
00:08:17,283 --> 00:08:23,957
(QUEEN NEHALENNIA) <i>The sacred</i>
<i>flames prevented the Queen of</i>
<i>Darkness from acquiring the</i>
<i>Golden Crystal... What's more...</i>

63
00:08:24,024 --> 00:08:28,829
<i>the Queen of the White Moon</i>
<i>sealed her away in the Darkness</i>
<i>of the New Moon!</i>

64
00:08:30,296 --> 00:08:37,303
But the Queen of Darkness simply
bided her time and awaited her
chance... She knew that if she
had the Golden Crystal...

65
00:08:37,403 --> 00:08:39,472
<i>she could break free of her</i>
<i>prison.</i>

66
00:08:41,474 --> 00:08:45,979
<i>Then, when the solar eclipse</i>
<i>she'd been waiting for</i>
<i>occurred...she unleashed her</i>
<i>minions...</i>

67
00:08:46,046 --> 00:08:48,815
[laughter]

68
00:08:48,882 --> 00:08:51,885
...and succeeded in making that
young man her prisoner!

69
00:08:52,152 --> 00:08:56,322
What happened to you wasn't
Helios's fault! So why don't you
let him go!

70
00:08:57,190 --> 00:09:01,001
You're right. My real grudge is
with those of the White Moon.

71
00:09:01,234 --> 00:09:03,504
And the time for revenge has
come!

72
00:09:03,570 --> 00:09:06,006
[pained screams]

73
00:09:06,106 --> 00:09:09,543
They will all have a taste of my
vengeance, beginning with you!

74
00:09:09,943 --> 00:09:13,346
No matter what you do to me, you
won't get your way‐‐! [pained
scream]

75
00:09:13,413 --> 00:09:15,916
No one who defies me will go
unpunished!

76
00:09:16,016 --> 00:09:20,921
[pained screams and passing out]

77
00:09:21,622 --> 00:09:22,355
Hmph!

78
00:09:24,290 --> 00:09:25,358
Zirconia!

79
00:09:25,425 --> 00:09:27,027
I am here, my queen!

80
00:09:27,293 --> 00:09:29,029
You've done well,

81
00:09:29,229 --> 00:09:31,031
Your majesty is too kind.

82
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:36,870
But the other people of the
White Moon are still alive out
there. Get rid of them at once.

83
00:09:37,203 --> 00:09:38,038
My queen.

84
00:09:38,972 --> 00:09:41,207
(JUN‐JUN) <i>Man! This totally</i>
<i>sucks!</i>

85
00:09:42,408 --> 00:09:44,210
Yes, it's very disappointing.

86
00:09:44,277 --> 00:09:46,547
Palla‐Palla wants to ride
Pegasus!

87
00:09:46,613 --> 00:09:49,382
She's cut us out of the loop!
It's so unfair!

88
00:09:49,449 --> 00:09:49,883
Mhm!

89
00:09:50,483 --> 00:09:52,052
I say we go tell her off!

90
00:09:53,554 --> 00:09:56,222
Forget it. You shouldn't even be
thinking about defying Queen
Nehalennia.

91
00:09:56,422 --> 00:09:57,490
By the way...

92
00:09:57,591 --> 00:09:58,992
...what is that thing...

93
00:09:59,092 --> 00:09:59,993
...you're making there?

94
00:10:00,093 --> 00:10:01,835
Something to look at stars with.

95
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:02,836
Something to what?

96
00:10:03,737 --> 00:10:05,506
I thought I'd expand my horizons
a little.

97
00:10:06,507 --> 00:10:08,842
It's done! The peeking Orb!

98
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:10,343
Well, isn't that odd.

99
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:11,177
(JUN‐JUN) <i>Hey!</i>

100
00:10:11,945 --> 00:10:12,245
(PALLA‐PALLA) <i>You shouldn't spy!</i>

101
00:10:13,346 --> 00:10:14,014
(CERE‐CERE) <i>I'll tell Queen</i>
<i>Nehalennia.</i>

102
00:10:14,915 --> 00:10:17,851
I can't seem to adjust it right.
Oh, dear.

103
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:20,020
I get it.

104
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:21,522
That is a problem.

105
00:10:22,589 --> 00:10:25,191
Let's see. Cloning Orb!

106
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:31,865
Well, look at that!

107
00:10:31,932 --> 00:10:32,533
Not bad.

108
00:10:34,067 --> 00:10:37,403
But, what if Queen Nehalennia
mistook it for the real one by
mistake? May I?

109
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:39,372
Open Orb.

110
00:10:42,442 --> 00:10:44,044
(PALLA‐PALLA) Applause!
Applause!

111
00:10:44,110 --> 00:10:45,045
Hush!

112
00:10:45,946 --> 00:10:47,881
[chuckle and grunt]

113
00:10:50,584 --> 00:10:53,620
Oh no, now anybody could just
sneak right in there.

114
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:57,057
After all the trouble the queen
went through to capture her...

115
00:10:57,123 --> 00:11:00,226
...what if some bad kids came
along and pulled a swap?

116
00:11:00,293 --> 00:11:01,401
Yeah, but of course...

117
00:11:01,502 --> 00:11:03,069
...that would never be us.

118
00:11:03,169 --> 00:11:04,070
Of course not!

119
00:11:05,238 --> 00:11:06,573
(QUEEN NEHALENNIA) <i>There's no</i>
<i>escape for you now.</i>

120
00:11:08,274 --> 00:11:11,912
I may not have a beautiful
dream, but with the power of
Darkness that I now possess...

121
00:11:11,978 --> 00:11:15,649
I'm more than strong enough to
bend the Golden Crystal to my
will.

122
00:11:16,082 --> 00:11:18,251
But first to deal with you
people.

123
00:12:06,206 --> 00:12:08,074
What are all these mirrors for?

124
00:12:08,174 --> 00:12:10,210
(MAKOTO) <i>Someone must be</i>
<i>pretty into themselves.</i>

125
00:12:10,310 --> 00:12:11,678
(REI) <i>Sailor Moon, you coming?</i>

126
00:12:12,145 --> 00:12:13,313
Oh. Yeah, wait up!

127
00:12:28,494 --> 00:12:30,997
Just you wait, little girls...

128
00:12:32,666 --> 00:12:35,001
[grunts]

129
00:12:38,539 --> 00:12:42,676
Go forth! Go forth and destroy
those cursed brats!

130
00:12:43,343 --> 00:12:45,011
<i>Where did everyone go?</i>

131
00:12:47,781 --> 00:12:48,682
[uneasy breath]

132
00:12:51,284 --> 00:12:52,519
That you, Sailor Moon?

133
00:12:55,789 --> 00:12:57,357
Girls?

134
00:12:58,191 --> 00:13:00,066
I seem to have lost them.

135
00:13:02,603 --> 00:13:05,706
How did we all get seperated?
[gasp]

136
00:13:10,210 --> 00:13:11,545
<i>Sailor Jupiter.</i>

137
00:13:11,612 --> 00:13:12,546
Huh?

138
00:13:13,814 --> 00:13:14,715
<i>Behind you.</i>

139
00:13:17,283 --> 00:13:17,784
It's me.

140
00:13:18,118 --> 00:13:18,719
[gasp]

141
00:13:19,219 --> 00:13:21,387
Come on. Don't be afraid.

142
00:13:22,222 --> 00:13:23,389
I'm you, Jupiter.

143
00:13:24,224 --> 00:13:25,225
You're me?

144
00:13:26,159 --> 00:13:30,396
That's right. I'm you... The
real you.

145
00:13:32,432 --> 00:13:38,605
Why am I fighting as a Guardian
in this costume? It isn't really
me, I'm much more feminine than
this.

146
00:13:39,105 --> 00:13:44,745
My dream is a life surrounded by
flowers and sweets. But no one
undertands me...

147
00:13:44,811 --> 00:13:50,517
<i>How am I supposed to become the</i>
<i>girl I wish to be, if all I ever</i>
<i>do it fight?</i>

148
00:13:52,252 --> 00:13:53,587
[chuckle] <i>Look.</i>

149
00:13:54,254 --> 00:13:54,755
Huh?

150
00:13:56,823 --> 00:13:58,258
Gorgeous, right?

151
00:13:59,860 --> 00:14:00,601
[gasp]

152
00:14:01,602 --> 00:14:04,170
Why can't I dress like this in
the real world?

153
00:14:04,705 --> 00:14:06,272
We should just quit.

154
00:14:06,439 --> 00:14:08,108
What do you mean quit?

155
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:14,781
[chuckle] Quit all this silly
fighting and come join me... in
a wonderful dream.

156
00:14:22,556 --> 00:14:25,458
<i>Do I really have time for all</i>
<i>this nonsense?</i>

157
00:14:26,159 --> 00:14:29,462
My real dream, has always been
to become a doctor, right?

158
00:14:29,863 --> 00:14:32,833
Have I really decided to throw
away my dream?

159
00:14:33,466 --> 00:14:35,636
Throw away.. my dream...?

160
00:14:37,638 --> 00:14:44,244
We both know all the sacrifices
we've had to make fighting for
the people. And what do we get
for it?

161
00:14:45,378 --> 00:14:49,482
Let's ditch this bunch of
ingrates and live for our own
dream.

162
00:14:52,686 --> 00:14:57,658
Of course I'm afraid. There's no
guarantee that we'll win every
battle.

163
00:14:58,224 --> 00:15:00,567
We could even die in the next
one.

164
00:15:02,536 --> 00:15:04,404
Makes me want to run away.

165
00:15:04,871 --> 00:15:06,339
Run away...

166
00:15:08,942 --> 00:15:18,351
(YOUNG SAILOR GUARDIANS)
[laughter]

167
00:15:18,519 --> 00:15:21,688
Huh? [gasp]

168
00:15:23,624 --> 00:15:25,692
You're scared, right? I can
tell.

169
00:15:25,759 --> 00:15:26,359
Who‐‐?

170
00:15:26,893 --> 00:15:27,861
I'm you, Sailor Moon.

171
00:15:28,529 --> 00:15:29,362
You're me...?

172
00:15:30,196 --> 00:15:32,533
That's right. I know all about
you.

173
00:15:32,866 --> 00:15:34,701
You don't want to be here.

174
00:15:36,803 --> 00:15:39,873
<i>...Let's go away and dream, our</i>
<i>own dream together...</i>

175
00:15:42,442 --> 00:15:43,810
Our own dream...?

176
00:15:45,245 --> 00:15:48,882
That's right. Forget everything
else... and dream a wonderful
dream.

177
00:15:57,724 --> 00:15:58,725
(MAMORU) <i>Usako...</i>

178
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:00,567
[gasp]

179
00:16:00,934 --> 00:16:02,903
<i>Sailor Moon! Help me!</i>

180
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:05,739
[choked up gasps]

181
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,743
What's worng? Does it hurt
somewhere?

182
00:16:10,476 --> 00:16:12,913
[catching breath]

183
00:16:13,514 --> 00:16:14,480
Can't you tell?

184
00:16:14,581 --> 00:16:15,248
[taken aback]

185
00:16:16,617 --> 00:16:19,419
You know all about me, but you
don't understand the pain I
feel?

186
00:16:20,921 --> 00:16:23,924
<i>Mamo, your pain is my pain.</i>

187
00:16:26,827 --> 00:16:27,761
Usako...

188
00:16:30,030 --> 00:16:33,266
As a child, I didn't have to
worry about anything.

189
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:37,604
But now, I have friends to share
all my joys and sorrows with.

190
00:16:38,605 --> 00:16:45,278
<i>And I wouldn't have it any other</i>
<i>way. I don't regret who I am</i>
<i>now... Not for a second!</i>

191
00:16:45,712 --> 00:16:46,446
[grunt]

192
00:16:47,113 --> 00:16:47,881
(USAGI) <i>You are not me!</i>

193
00:16:48,615 --> 00:16:50,551
So let's see who you really are!

194
00:16:51,317 --> 00:16:54,788
Moon Tiara Action!

195
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:56,456
[flinching]

196
00:17:00,567 --> 00:17:01,802
Wretched brat!

197
00:17:02,636 --> 00:17:03,469
(MINAKO) <i>Venus...!</i>

198
00:17:08,408 --> 00:17:10,476
...Love and Beauty Shock!

199
00:17:13,714 --> 00:17:14,648
Mercury...!

200
00:17:16,482 --> 00:17:18,819
...Aqua Rhapsody!

201
00:17:23,423 --> 00:17:23,990
[grunt]

202
00:17:26,426 --> 00:17:27,493
Everyone!

203
00:17:28,595 --> 00:17:31,665
You thought you could trick us
with your spell, huh?

204
00:17:31,765 --> 00:17:33,333
Don't underestimate the Sailor
Guardians!

205
00:17:33,433 --> 00:17:35,702
We haven't forgotten the dreams
of our childhood!

206
00:17:35,836 --> 00:17:37,838
And we never will. But right
now...

207
00:17:37,938 --> 00:17:40,507
...we have a much greater dream
to fulfill!

208
00:17:40,674 --> 00:17:46,513
Dream on! None of you is ever
going to make it out of this
labyrinth alive! I'll see to
that!

209
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:47,514
(REI) What the...!

210
00:17:47,614 --> 00:17:48,515
(AMI) <i>Is that...?</i>

211
00:17:48,582 --> 00:17:49,382
(USAGI) It's Chibi Moon!

212
00:17:49,516 --> 00:17:50,350
[gasps]

213
00:17:51,451 --> 00:17:52,418
Chibi Moon!...

214
00:17:52,919 --> 00:17:54,521
<i>Wake up, Chibi Moon!</i>

215
00:17:54,855 --> 00:17:56,623
Now he's finally ours!

216
00:17:56,723 --> 00:17:57,524
So pretty!

217
00:17:58,291 --> 00:17:59,860
I get to ride him first!
[chuckle]

218
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:02,736
‐Hey!
‐No fair!
[grunts]

219
00:18:02,869 --> 00:18:05,539
Whoah! [pained grunts and
groans]

220
00:18:06,707 --> 00:18:09,710
Oh, that's right, Pegasus
doesn't have a physical body.

221
00:18:13,213 --> 00:18:14,881
What're you looking at, huh?

222
00:18:14,948 --> 00:18:16,983
Hey, is he making fun of us?!

223
00:18:17,483 --> 00:18:20,386
In case you haven't noticed, we
captured your host.

224
00:18:20,887 --> 00:18:25,125
Yeah, so you better do as we
say, or else‐‐... Are you even
<i>listening?</i>

225
00:18:25,225 --> 00:18:28,394
Not the most cooperative horse
in the world, is he?

226
00:18:28,895 --> 00:18:30,897
Fine then . Leash Orb!

227
00:18:35,769 --> 00:18:38,572
(VES‐VES) Even you can't get out
of that, Pegasus.

228
00:18:38,639 --> 00:18:41,975
You're going to be our pet,
whether you like it or not.

229
00:18:44,911 --> 00:18:45,746
Huh?

230
00:18:48,081 --> 00:18:49,916
Wow. Pretty horn.

231
00:18:50,617 --> 00:18:52,085
Hey, is that what I think it is?

232
00:18:52,252 --> 00:18:54,087
It must be the Golden Crystal!

233
00:18:54,788 --> 00:18:56,422
Y'think it comes off?

234
00:18:56,523 --> 00:18:57,423
Mmm...

235
00:19:00,801 --> 00:19:01,768
I'm taking it!

236
00:19:01,835 --> 00:19:03,103
‐Hey!
‐No fair!
‐Huh?

237
00:19:03,169 --> 00:19:05,471
[chuckles and arguing]

238
00:19:07,874 --> 00:19:10,777
Ahhh! [grunts]

239
00:19:14,715 --> 00:19:15,782
That was rude.

240
00:19:16,817 --> 00:19:18,785
I am really not liking your
attitude, Pegasus.

241
00:19:18,852 --> 00:19:19,953
Palla‐Palla got a burn!

242
00:19:20,053 --> 00:19:21,622
Let's teach him a lesson.

243
00:19:21,722 --> 00:19:22,889
Go... tighter!

244
00:19:28,194 --> 00:19:28,895
[groggy groan]

245
00:19:31,998 --> 00:19:33,900
Pegasus? Pegasus!

246
00:19:34,835 --> 00:19:37,170
<i>Stop it! What are you doing to</i>
<i>him?!</i>

247
00:19:37,971 --> 00:19:40,974
Hey, we didn't start that fire,
don't go blaming us.

248
00:19:41,074 --> 00:19:41,474
Huh?

249
00:19:43,009 --> 00:19:44,978
Yeah, he's the one who set
himself abalaze, tell him to
stop it.

250
00:19:45,045 --> 00:19:45,812
And soon, or‐‐

251
00:19:46,647 --> 00:19:47,914
‐‐he's going to be a barbecued
horsey.

252
00:19:48,314 --> 00:19:48,849
[gasp]

253
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:56,056
(JUN‐JUN) <i>Actually, I think</i>
<i>it's too late anyway.</i>

254
00:19:56,156 --> 00:19:58,859
(VES‐VES) Guess we'll just have
to watch him die.

255
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:03,504
Pegasus! [grunts]

256
00:20:05,539 --> 00:20:07,774
[grunts]

257
00:20:09,876 --> 00:20:11,111
I don't believe it...

258
00:20:11,211 --> 00:20:12,846
She ran into the fire.

259
00:20:12,946 --> 00:20:15,616
[grunts]

260
00:20:16,016 --> 00:20:17,117
Chibi Moon!

261
00:20:18,619 --> 00:20:29,796
[grunts]

262
00:20:30,496 --> 00:20:31,464
Hmmm?

263
00:20:34,701 --> 00:20:36,136
Oh, Pegasus...

264
00:20:38,505 --> 00:20:39,673
I don't get it...

265
00:20:40,306 --> 00:20:43,476
Why would you risk your own life
like that?

266
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:49,149
What do you mean, "why?" I
didn't even think about it... I
just wanted to save Pegasus.

267
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:50,984
(ZIRCONIA) <i>Girls!</i>

268
00:20:51,151 --> 00:20:51,985
Uh‐oh!

269
00:20:53,319 --> 00:20:55,989
What have you done, you
insuffereably insolent and
stupid fools?!

270
00:20:56,056 --> 00:20:57,658
Huh?! Ahhh!

271
00:21:01,001 --> 00:21:03,670
[gasp and scream]

272
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:05,506
Chibi Moon! No!

273
00:21:05,839 --> 00:21:16,182
[screaming and passing out]

274
00:21:17,851 --> 00:21:18,519
No!

275
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:21,522
[gasps]

276
00:21:25,759 --> 00:21:26,860
Chibi Moon...

277
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:35,702
Hey, let us out of here, Granny!

278
00:21:35,769 --> 00:21:39,205
Don't worry, Queen Nehalennia
will get us out of here for
sure!

279
00:21:39,305 --> 00:21:42,709
Oh, yes, of course she will.
Right, Jun‐Jun? Hello?

280
00:21:42,976 --> 00:21:44,044
What's wrong Jun‐Jun?

281
00:21:44,144 --> 00:21:45,779
Is something on your mind?

282
00:21:46,046 --> 00:21:48,715
That little one they call Chibi
Moon...

283
00:21:48,915 --> 00:21:49,550
Hmmm?

284
00:21:51,251 --> 00:21:55,055
We're definitely stronger than
she is, but somehow it's like
she's better than us.

285
00:21:55,221 --> 00:21:56,723
Y'know what I mean?

286
00:21:57,658 --> 00:21:58,559
Mm‐hm.

287
00:23:53,353 --> 00:23:56,790
(QUEEN NEHALENNIA) <i>The time has</i>
<i>come to break this loathsome</i>
<i>seal.</i>

288
00:23:56,890 --> 00:24:00,093
<i>Not even the Golden Crystal's</i>
<i>sacred flames can stop me now.</i>

289
00:24:00,193 --> 00:24:06,873
(USAGI) <i>No. The Golden Crystal</i>
<i>embodies the beautiful dreams of</i>
<i>people living on Earth! I won't</i>
<i>let you take away their dreams!</i>

290
00:24:06,940 --> 00:24:11,311
(QUEEN NEHALENNIA) <i>You fool!</i>
<i>Helios, this world, and the</i>
<i>Golden Crystal will all be mine!</i>

291
00:24:11,411 --> 00:24:16,216
(USAGI) <i>Next time on Sailor Moon</i>
<i>SuperS, "The Golden Crystal</i>
<i>Appears: Nehalennia's Magic."</i>

292
00:24:16,282 --> 00:24:18,384
<i>The moonlight is a messanger</i>
<i>of love.</i>

